Endangered Species Act of 1973 (


   16 U.S.C. 1531


et seq.);

The National Historic Preservation Act (


   16 U.S.C. 470


et seq.);

Farmland Protection Policy Act (


   7 U.S.C. 4201


et seq.);

 The issuance of bulletins and information publications that do not
concern environmental matters or substantial facility design,
construction, or maintenance practices;

 Purchase of land where use shall remain unchanged, or the purchase
of existing water rights where no associated construction is
involved;

 Studies and engineering undertaken to define proposed actions or
alternatives sufficiently so that environmental effects can be
assessed;

 Construction of electric power lines within the fenced area of an
existing substation, switching station, or within the boundaries of
an electric generating facility site;

 Management actions relating to invitation for bids, award of
contracts, and the actual physical commencement of construction
activities;

 Construction of microwave facilities, SCADA, and energy management
systems involving no more than five acres (2 hectares) of physical
disturbance at any single site;

 Construction of cooperative or company headquarters, maintenance
facilities, or other buildings involving no more than 10 acres (4
hectares) of physical disturbance or fenced property;

 Construction of cooperative headquarters, maintenance, and
equipment storage facilities involving more than 10 acres (4
hectares) of physical disturbance or fenced property;
